final_hyps.green: The green object is the Goal that the agent must reach.
final_hyps.brown: Brown objects are False Walls. The agent can move through False Walls.
final_hyps.yellow: The yellow object is a Key. The agent can pick up the Key by moving into its space. While holding the Key, the agent is colored purple.
final_hyps.cyan: The cyan object is a KeyDoor. When the agent moves onto this object, the KeyDoor opens and the Key is destroyed. The agent cannot move through the KeyDoor while it is closed.

solve_plan: First, determine that the green object is the Goal object. Then, align the agent on the horizontal axis (y=8) since the yellow object and cyan object are also at y=8. The agent does not need to move vertically. Next, move the agent to pick up the Key by moving RIGHT. Because the agent is at x=5, it must move RIGHT 13 - 5 = 8 times to reach the yellow object. After picking up the Key, the agent will be colored purple. Then, move the agent to open the KeyDoor by moving RIGHT again. Because the agent is now at x=13, it must move RIGHT 18 - 13 = 5 times to reach the cyan object. After opening the KeyDoor, the agent can move through it. Finally, move the agent to reach the goal (x=19) by moving RIGHT again. Because the agent is now at x=18, it must move RIGHT 19 - 18 = 1 time to reach the green object. Then, move DOWN to align with the green object on the vertical axis (y=10). Because the agent is currently at y=8, it must move DOWN 10 - 8 = 2 times.
